snippet.textDisplay:
Biggest myths ?

Colouring each confirmed case(s) of a country red is a bit scaremongering. It looks like for example the whole of Australia has the coronavirus, even the red centre.

Maybe best to put a red dot relative size to the number of cases, on say Sydney or Frankfurt where it's diagnosed.

Facts and not scaremongering.
